faqs:
  - title: What security certifications does Optimizely hold?
    description: >
      Optimizely holds comprehensive certifications including ISO 27001:2022 
      (ISMS), ISO 27017:2015 (Cloud Security), ISO 27018:2019 (PII Protection), 
      SOC 2 Type 2 (all products), PCI DSS v4.0.1 (QSA-audited for Web/Feature 
      Exp, Self-Assessment for Commerce), TISAX (Campaign), HIPAA/BAA support 
      (CMS, Web & Feature Exp), and CSA STAR Level 1 (CAIQ 4.0). All certifications 
      performed by independent third-party auditors and available upon request.
  - title: Where is customer data hosted?
    description: >
      Customer data hosted on enterprise cloud platforms (Azure, Google Cloud, 
      AWS) with multi-region options across North America, Europe, Middle East, 
      and Asia Pacific. Customers can select their preferred data hosting region. 
      Geo-fencing enables EU or US data location choice. Optimizely is EU-U.S. 
      Data Privacy Framework certified for data transfers.
  - title: How does Optimizely handle penetration testing?
    description: >
      Annual third-party application security assessments and penetration tests 
      performed by CREST-accredited penetration testing providers. Tests cover 
      infrastructure, applications, and security controls. Software security 
      measured using BSIMM (Building Security In Maturity Model). Reports with 
      issue disposition available on request.
  - title: What authentication methods are supported?
    description: >
      Optimizely supports multiple authentication methods: (1) Password authentication 
      with 8+ character minimum, complexity requirements, rate limiting, and hashed 
      storage with salt; (2) 2-step verification via mobile phone temporary codes; 
      (3) Single Sign-On (SSO) via SAML 2.0 for corporate credentials. Employees 
      use SSO, strong passwords, and two-factor authentication for production access.
  - title: How does Optimizely protect data in transit and at rest?
    description: >
      Data encrypted in transit using Transport Layer Security (TLS) with regular 
      updates to cipher suites and configurations. All visitor data stored by 
      Optimizely and third-party providers encrypted at rest. Communications from 
      end-users encrypted by default using industry-standard encryption technology.
  - title: What is Optimizely's incident response process?
    description: >
      Comprehensive 24/7 Incident Response Plan with advanced threat detection 
      technology (IDS, SIEM). Security Team investigates, isolates, and mitigates 
      identified events. Customers informed per agreement terms. Plan tested and 
      refined regularly. Access logs retained minimum 6 months for forensics. 
      Security incidents reportable to securityeng@optimizely.com.
  - title: How does Optimizely ensure business continuity?
    description: >
      Business Continuity and Disaster Recovery (BCDR) program with state-of-art 
      cloud providers (Azure, GCP, AWS), data replication within and across 
      multiple data centers, frequent tested backups, global team resource shifting, 
      and continuity plans for service disruptions. Security maintained during DR 
      operations. Customer-facing DR reports available on request.
  - title: Does Optimizely support HIPAA compliance?
    description: >
      Yes. Optimizely supports HIPAA compliance as Business Associate with signed 
      Business Associate Agreements (BAA) for enterprise customers. HIPAA-ready 
      Software Services include Content Management System (PaaS & SaaS) and Web & 
      Feature Experimentation Services. Implements technical and organizational 
      safeguards for Protected Health Information (PHI) and ePHI with breach 
      notification without undue delay.
  - title: What is Optimizely's AI ethics policy?
    description: >
      Optimizely follows comprehensive AI Ethics Policy with seven principles: 
      (1) Privacy - existing controls enforced, customer data segregated; (2) Security - 
      data protected with same security controls; (3) Transparency - AI use disclosed, 
      customers can disable; (4) Humanism - human review and control; (5) Fairness - 
      bias evaluation and reporting; (6) Quality - testing and monitoring for drift; 
      (7) Risk - intellectual property respect and risk management. Policy effective 
      July 2024.
  - title: How does Optimizely handle risk management?
    description: >
      Security Team conducts periodic risk assessments using ISO 27005:2018 methodology. 
      Top risks identified with risk treatment plans prepared. Risk assessment, top 
      risk selection, and treatment plans reviewed and tracked by Security Governance 
      Board. Continuous monitoring, internal and external audits ensure compliance 
      and security protocol effectiveness.
